# Nursy AI Product & Build Guide

## Product Vision

Nursy AI is a mobile-first, offline-capable AI health companion that helps users track daily health status, symptoms, medications, emergency health details, and health trends.

The product is designed for real-world low-connectivity use.

```text
Mobile-first, offline-first, cloud-enhanced.
```

## System Strategy

### 1. Android App Is The Product

The Kotlin + Jetpack Compose Android app is the daily user experience. It must work without internet.

Core local capabilities:

- profile and emergency health card
- daily health check-ins
- symptom tracking
- medication management
- local dashboard and timeline
- reminders and notifications
- local rules and symptom parser

### 2. AWS Is The Support Layer

AWS should only provide:

- authentication
- backup
- sync
- recovery on a new device
- optional report generation

The recommended backend is Cognito, API Gateway HTTP API, Lambda, and DynamoDB. Keep it serverless and low-cost.

### 3. Cloud AI Is Optional Premium Intelligence

Cloud AI should not run for every journal note or screen load. It should generate occasional reports from compact structured data:

- weekly health summary
- monthly trend report
- medication adherence explanation
- symptom trend explanation

Local AI handles daily value. Cloud AI improves reports when credits or a paid plan allow it.

